WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.780 --> 00:00:04.630
&gt;&gt; From the Library of
Congress in Washington, D.C.

00:00:19.250 --> 00:00:21.290
&gt;&gt; Edward Widner: Good
afternoon everyone.

00:00:21.290 --> 00:00:24.120
Welcome to LJ119.

00:00:24.120 --> 00:00:26.080
My name's Ted Widner.

00:00:26.080 --> 00:00:28.970
I'm the director of the
John W. Kluge Center.

00:00:28.970 --> 00:00:33.690
And if you grew up in New England
like I did, this time of year,

00:00:33.690 --> 00:00:37.450
April 19th -- specifically
the night of April 18th

00:00:37.450 --> 00:00:41.770
to 19th is the night some of
us remember as the outbreak

00:00:41.770 --> 00:00:47.310
of hostilities in 1775 and
switched to a military phase

00:00:47.310 --> 00:00:51.170
of the long conflict between
the colonies and Great Britain.

00:00:51.170 --> 00:00:56.690 position:56%
It's now sort of developed into
just a marathon and a lot of parties

00:00:56.690 --> 00:01:00.360
around Boston, and not too many
people remember the political

00:01:00.360 --> 00:01:03.310
circumstances of April 1775.

00:01:03.310 --> 00:01:05.090
But I can guarantee you, one person

00:01:05.090 --> 00:01:08.170
in this room knows
them very, very well.

00:01:08.170 --> 00:01:13.320
It's such a pleasure to introduce
to you T.H. Breen of Timothy Breen,

00:01:13.320 --> 00:01:15.820
who is the John Kluge
professor of American law

00:01:15.820 --> 00:01:18.910
and governance here
at the Kluge Center.

00:01:18.910 --> 00:01:21.620
He's also the William Smith
Mason Professor Emeritus

00:01:21.620 --> 00:01:23.990
at Northwestern University.

00:01:23.990 --> 00:01:28.770 position:56%
He's the James Marsh Professor at
large, at the University of Vermont,

00:01:28.770 --> 00:01:32.630
and that is -- that has to be the
greatest job anyone could ever have

00:01:32.630 --> 00:01:36.920
to be a Professor at Large and
that is what he's been for us.

00:01:36.920 --> 00:01:38.230
He's covered the waterfront.

00:01:38.230 --> 00:01:42.220
He's been inspiring presence
among us at our lunches

00:01:42.220 --> 00:01:45.150
and in the hallway,
striking up conversations.

00:01:45.150 --> 00:01:47.620
The Kluge Center has a lot of
different kinds of scholars

00:01:47.620 --> 00:01:49.290
in different disciplines

00:01:49.290 --> 00:01:54.990
and Timothy's been just a
wonderful addition to our mix.

00:01:54.990 --> 00:01:56.650
Many of you know his work already.

00:01:56.650 --> 00:01:58.420
Many of you are personal
friends of his,

00:01:58.420 --> 00:02:00.960
