at the end of the war and went

00:49:15.540 --> 00:49:19.150
to Nova Scotia or other places,
sometimes to the Caribbean.

00:49:19.150 --> 00:49:25.540
And of that group, a huge
number were not eager to go,

00:49:25.540 --> 00:49:28.150
because they were the slaves
owned by these people.

00:49:28.150 --> 00:49:30.410
So whatever the number is.

00:49:30.410 --> 00:49:34.920
But the research that I've done
shows that the great majority

00:49:34.920 --> 00:49:38.800
of people that had participated
as enemies of the revolution

00:49:38.800 --> 00:49:43.520
in some demonstrable way either
giving aid and comfort to the enemy

00:49:43.520 --> 00:49:48.420
or perhaps even serving in
one of their loyalist legions,

00:49:48.420 --> 00:49:53.960
far exceeded, far, far
exceeded that 60,000 number.

00:49:53.960 --> 00:49:58.460 position:56%
And this set off a very forgotten --

00:49:58.460 --> 00:50:01.860
thankfully it's forgotten
because now I can write my book --

00:50:01.860 --> 00:50:07.440
but the first rate
refugee crisis in America.

00:50:07.440 --> 00:50:10.690
Because these people that had
been enemies of the revolution --

00:50:10.690 --> 00:50:13.720
and some of them had done
some very bad things --

00:50:13.720 --> 00:50:15.580
they wanted to come home.

00:50:15.580 --> 00:50:18.240
They wanted to live with their
neighbors they had violated,

00:50:18.240 --> 00:50:20.430
and humiliated, and hurt.

00:50:20.430 --> 00:50:24.180
And the ordinary people
of American said, no way.

00:50:24.180 --> 00:50:25.480
No way.

00:50:25.480 --> 00:50:29.140
It was the leaders and the people
that signed the peace treaty

00:50:29.140 --> 00:50:36.670
in Paris that said -- as all
political documents like this,

00:50:36.670 --> 00:50:38.940
the language is very wishy washy --

00:50:38.940 --> 00:50:44.660
but that Congress of the
United States would recommend

00:50:44.660 --> 00:50:49.560 position:56%
to the separate state governments
that they would not pursue loyalists

00:50:49.560 --> 00:50:52.610
or any other people who had
acted against the interests

00:50:52.610 --> 00:50:55.970
of the United States
before the peace treaty.

00:50:55.970 --> 00:50:59.190
The people were not happy to
hear this and there were many,

00:50:59.190 --> 00:51:01.700
many incidents of local violence.

00:51:01.700 --> 00:51:05.330
The Sons of Liberty, which
we associate with the lead

00:51:05.330 --> 00:51:10.250
up to the revolution
reformed in Boston in 1783

00:51:10.250 --> 00:51:14.070
to keep the refugees out.

00:51:14.070 --> 00:51:21.950 position:56%
But in time -- by 1786 remarkably --
I think people -- they wanted farms,

00:51:21.950 --> 00:51:24.790
they wanted to go west,
they wanted to say hello

00:51:24.790 --> 00:51:26.430
to all these kids they're having.

00:51:26.430 --> 00:51:35.500
Whatever they did, the hatred
dissipated, and so it's true

00:51:35.500 --> 00:51:38.920
that for instance,
some of the leaders

00:51:38.920 --> 00:51:42.560
in the Washington cabinet
were Tories.

00:51:42.560 --> 00:51:46.070
They had, you know, come back.

00:51:46.070 --> 00:51:50.040
Trench Cocks is one
economic analysis.

00:51:50.040 --> 00:51:54.340
The point is for a concatenation
of elements in our country --

00:51:54.340 --> 00:51:56.710
and I think probably
it was its size.

00:51:56.710 --> 00:51:58.660 position:56%
Because what happened to the Tories?

00:51:58.660 --> 00:52:02.920
My answer is usually -- and
it's very glib -- is Ohio.

00:52:02.920 --> 00:52:11.680
But people found other things
to do than pursue revenge.

00:52:11.680 --> 00:52:13.320
If I may -- I don't think --

00:52:13.320 --> 00:52:18.950
I'll maybe end with a story
I found in my research here.

00:52:18.950 --> 00:52:27.380 position:56%
Some of the hottest, my physical
violent, horrible crimes of neighbor

00:52:27.380 --> 00:52:30.270
against neighbor took place
in the American south.

00:52:30.270 --> 00:52:35.300
Georgia, South Carolina,
especially up country Carolina.

00:52:35.300 --> 00:52:36.900
There's a town there that some

00:52:36.900 --> 00:52:39.570
of you may have gone
to called Ninety-six.

00:52:39.570 --> 00:52:43.320
People think I'm making it up,
but it is a town and it's 96 miles

00:52:43.320 --> 00:52:47.280
